org.nerd4j.csv.parser

Interface CSVParser

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AutoCloseable, Closeable

    public interface CSVParser
extends Closeable
    CSVParser reads character data from a Reader, parsing and tokenizing them into CSVToken.

    After usage it should be closed to permit resource release.

    Author:
    Nerd4j Team

      • getCurrentToken

        CSVToken getCurrentToken()
        Returns last read CSVToken. If read() wasn't called before null will be returned.
        Returns:
        last read CSVToken.

      • getCurrentValue

        String getCurrentValue()
        Returns last read field value. If read() wasn't called before or getCurrentToken() isn't CSVToken.FIELD null will be returned.
        Returns:
        last read field value.

      • read

        CSVToken read()
              throws IOException
        Read the next CSVToken and returns it. The result CSVToken will be returned from getCurrentToken() too.
        Returns:
        next read CSVToken.
        Throws:
        IOException - if an error occurs while parsing data.

      • skip

        CSVToken skip()
              throws IOException
        Read the next CSVToken and returns it. The result CSVToken will be returned from getCurrentToken() too.

        The method getCurrentValue() won't return any value.

        Returns:
        next read CSVToken.
        Throws:
        IOException - if an error occurs while parsing data.
